5 Ss
	Identify , review and remove waste
	Use the "Five Ss" (5S): This is a key housekeeping technique for workplace organization that helps eliminate waste:
	Seiri (Sort): Remove unnecessary items from the work area.
	Seiton (Set in order): Organize remaining items so they are easily accessible and have a designated place.
	Seiso (Shine/Scrub): Keep the workplace clean and tidy to easily spot defects or issues.
	Seiketsu (Standardize): Create procedures to maintain the first three Ss consistently.
	Shitsuke (Sustain): Foster a culture that maintains the improvements over time.
